Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
timing_pba_ex...h_nworst_limit(25.10)    timing_pba_ex...h_nworst_limit(25.10)

Name
       timing_pba_exhaustive_path_nworst_limit

Syntax
       timing_pba_exhaustive_path_nworst_limit <value>

       Default: 10000

       Specifies  the  maximum number of paths per endpoint (nworst) that will
       be re-timed in exhaustive path-based analysis (PBA).

       In exhaustive PBA mode, the  value  specified  with  the  report_timing
       -nworst  parameter  is  used only during the final reporting. The value
       specified with the timing_pba_exhaustive_path_nworst_limit global vari-
       able (and not the report_timing -nworst value) is used to  specify  the
       maximum number of paths to be re-timed per endpoint.

       If  the  limit  specified by timing_pba_exhaustive_path_nworst_limit is
       reached  and   timing_path_based_enable_exhaustive_depth_bounded_by_gba
       global variable is set to:

              * true: The worst of the current PBA slack is used and N+1th GBA
                path is reported.

              * false:  The current PBA slack is reported - which may be opti-
                mistic.

       To set this global variable, use the set command.

